   <mods:abstract>Encloses petition by Messrs French and nephew, who had arrested Thomas
            Barclay, American consul general in France, for a debt of 67,206 pounds. Barclay
            released by the parliament of Guienne but the petitioners want to continue legal action
            against him. French minister removed obstacle to prosecution in this particular case.
            Thinks general resolution good idea, that consuls of the United States in foreign
            countries and vice-versa should be prosecuted for debt like other citizens and subjects
            in those places. Believes disadvantages of having foreign consuls in the United States
            outweigh benefits of having American consuls abroad.</mods:abstract>
